N0123NOISE.title: Am I Dead, Or In Hell
N0123NOISE.about:
Here it is! After the first two song EP, Infected Fetus, which is a collab project between N0123NOISE and ZoDiaCMaSSaCrE, are here with a 8 track album!
The story of this album is of a man who has died, but his mind and soul is still within his corpse. His body is completely motionless due to being brain dead, but he can still think and feel, from the insects feeding on his body to his body's own decomposition, he feels it all happening at once, along with the pain but he is helpless and can not stop it from happening. All he can do is just lay there and wonder, why is he still alive, and when will he finally die and go to hell.
[Story by ZoDiaCMaSSaCrE]
Infected Fetus is:
Zach (N0123NOISE): Noise, Drone, Samples, Artwork
Bunny (ZoDiaCMaSSaCrE): Remixing, Edits, Drone, Ambient

N0123NOISE.title: Just One Fall To End It All
N0123NOISE.about:
As I look down to the people walking, just living their lives thinking about nothing, I sit above them wondering, who would scream as they see me fall, who will try to catch me, and who will pull their phone out to record my suicide, it's something to think about as I begin to fall.
This split has been done for awhile but due to laziness and some really big issues in my life, it has been just sitting on my laptop for a month now, but here it is. Thanks to Bunny (ZoDiaCMaSSaCrE) for always being a great friend, always supporting me, and for doing a third split with me!
ZoDiaCMaSSaCrE side is live harsh noise he made using a mic and his laptop.
My side is depressing drone/dark ambient that'll make you depressed and feel alone.

N0123NOISE.title: When The Wind Blows
N0123NOISE.about:
Uploading here for archiving.
A tribute to my favorite movie, When the Wind Blows, a 1986 animated film about a elderly
couple who after surviving a nuclear attack, are trying to live out through the fallout and live with a sense of normality by following info and a list of rules giving to them by Government pamphlets on how to survive a nuclear attack, a big theme in the film is how you shouldn't always listen to your Government for even they don't know what to do in dark times.
Track one "Shall We Pray Dear?" was originally released by Earthwalker Recordings, featuring a sample from the ending of the film.
Track two "Believing Everything Will Be Ok" was originally released as a cd-r on Empty Shelters Records, featuring two samples, from the movie and the BBC Radio Play of the book.
